    "body": "@Pedro-vk Thanks for opening - this is a duplicate of #501. \r\n\r\nThe way async/await integrates with the migrations feature is confusing for a lot of users. `truffle-migrate` was written before `await` became common and it stages deployments as 'thennables' rather than executing them as true promises. See [this comment](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/501#issuecomment-332589663) for advice about how to resolve. ",
